The paper deals with deep learning techniques for 3D scene understanding, specifically semantic and instance segmentation of 3D point clouds. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also proposes a multi-value conditional random field model, which is a probabilistic graphical model, indicating a possible fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of high-dimensional embeddings suggests a possible fit for the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing techniques for incorporating semantic labels, indicating a possible fit for the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category.
